docs.abstract: An already busy start to the year for the tech sector is set to ramp up with the beginning of the tech earnings season this week.
docs.snippet: An already busy start to the year for the tech sector is set to ramp up with the beginning of the tech earnings season this week.
docs.lead_paragraph: Just 11 days into 2016, it has already been a busy period for tech news — and that’s about to ramp up further.

headline.main: Daily Report: The Tech News Cycle is About to Ramp Up

docs.abstract: Quarterly results underscored Microsoft’s good and bad trends as software floundered while the cloud business continued to grow.
docs.snippet: Quarterly results underscored Microsoft’s good and bad trends as software floundered while the cloud business continued to grow.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Satya Nadella has put cloud computing at the center of Microsoft’s strategy. It is a move that looks to be paying off, at least in the eyes of investors.

headline.main: Microsoft Profit and Revenue Fall, but Cloud Computing Grows
headline.print_headline: Cloud Business Lifts Microsoft’s Fortunes as Its Software Side Slides

docs.abstract: A Q. and A. with a notable book blogger (and Microsoft co-founder).
docs.snippet: A Q. and A. with a notable book blogger (and Microsoft co-founder).
docs.lead_paragraph: Bill Gates, the co-founder of Microsoft, has emerged as a force in the publishing industry, thanks to the book reviews he posts on his blog, Gates Notes. Mr. Gates, who says he reads about 50 books a year, discussed his love of reading, how he makes his selections and what book Warren Buffett recommended. Below are excerpts from a recent email interview.

headline.main: Bill Gates on Books and Blogging

docs.abstract: In an era of rising transparency and concerns about corporate ethics, companies eager to please millennials appear to be shifting business models and messages.
docs.snippet: In an era of rising transparency and concerns about corporate ethics, companies eager to please millennials appear to be shifting business models and messages.
docs.lead_paragraph: Way back in 2008, I wrote about Wal-Mart’s emerging effort to cut environmental and social harms from its business operations by exerting influence back along globe-spanning supply chains.

headline.main: With Imposed Transparency and Concerned Millennials, a Boom in Corporate Responsibility?

docs.abstract: Virtual assistants from tech behemoths including Apple, Microsoft, Amazon and Google are graded on their abilities to actually be of assistance.
docs.snippet: Virtual assistants from tech behemoths including Apple, Microsoft, Amazon and Google are graded on their abilities to actually be of assistance.
docs.lead_paragraph: WHEN I asked Alexa earlier this week who was playing in the Super Bowl, she responded, somewhat monotonously, “Super Bowl 49’s winner is New England Patriots.”

headline.main: Siri, Alexa and Other Virtual Assistants Put to the Test
headline.print_headline: Putting Virtual Assistants to the Test

docs.abstract: Microsoft has retired the Windows Media Center software, but other programs can manage your music, movies and photos in Windows 10.
docs.snippet: Microsoft has retired the Windows Media Center software, but other programs can manage your music, movies and photos in Windows 10.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. I use Windows Media Center to watch DVDs and listen to music on my Windows 7 laptop. Although I do not intend to upgrade to Windows 10 anytime soon, I have heard that the new system does not include WMC. Is this really true, and what are the alternatives?

docs.abstract: Microsoft hopes to give away its cloud services to 70,000 nonprofits in the next three years.
docs.snippet: Microsoft hopes to give away its cloud services to 70,000 nonprofits in the next three years.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Microsoft plans to give away $1 billion in cloud services to nonprofits and university researchers over the next three years, as the company updates its philanthropic initiatives to reflect shifts in technology.

headline.main: Microsoft to Donate $1 Billion in Cloud Services to Nonprofits and Researchers

docs.abstract: Investments in well-known tech giants like Amazon, Microsoft and Google fueled three top-performing funds in the fourth quarter.
docs.snippet: Investments in well-known tech giants like Amazon, Microsoft and Google fueled three top-performing funds in the fourth quarter.
docs.lead_paragraph: Bets on the biggest purveyors of technology — companies like Amazon, Google and Microsoft — powered three of the top-performing funds of the fourth quarter.

headline.main: Fund Managers Win With Tech Stalwarts and Burly Brand Names
headline.print_headline: Winning With Tech Stalwarts and Burly Brands

docs.abstract: Microsoft has been enthusiastically recommending upgrading to its Windows 10 operating system. But what if you’d rather not?
docs.snippet: Microsoft has been enthusiastically recommending upgrading to its Windows 10 operating system. But what if you’d rather not?
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. Is it true that Windows 10 will be a mandatory upgrade for Windows 7 and Windows 8 users this year? I have been getting the “invitation” to upgrade my Windows 7 computer for months, but have been avoiding it because I like my current system.

docs.abstract: Have the websites you want to see first loaded, each in its own tab, when you fire up Microsoft’s newest browser.
docs.snippet: Have the websites you want to see first loaded, each in its own tab, when you fire up Microsoft’s newest browser.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. Is there a way to make the Microsoft Edge browser in Windows 10 open multiple preset tabs when the program is started?

headline.main: Setting Up Tabs to Open Automatically in Microsoft Edge
